.TH "hsh Simple Shell" 1 "15 Abril 2020" "1.0"

.SH NAME
hsh - Luis Marin - Javier Jaramillo - Simple Shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
hsh (Basic shell that allows the entry of commands with simple arguments)

.SH DESCRIPTION
The project is presented to solve the end of term activity of Holberton School, this is intended to solve
the task of creating a basic minishel that allows the entry of arguments and can be read and executed by this
shell to show the results per screen.

.SH RETURN VALUE
The return value is based on each of the errors previously configured in our system and also a preconfigured CONTROL + D to stop the operation created.

.SH SYNTAX
#cisfun$ <command> <flags or options> <argument 1> <argument 2> ...
OR NON-INTERACTIVE MODE:
$ echo <command> | ./hsh
.SS

Interactive mode:
EXAMPLE 1:

$ ./hsh

#cisfun$ /bin/ls

hsh main.c shell.c

#cisfun$

#cisfun$ exit

$
.SS

Non-Interactive mode:

$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh

hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2

$

$ cat test_ls_2

/bin/ls

/bin/ls

$

$ cat test_ls_2 | ./hsh

hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2

hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2

$
.SS

.SH SEE ALSO
DASH(1)

